== 政府大臣 ==

=== 工作和养老金部副大臣 ===
2010年5月28日，格雷林宣誓加入[[英国枢密院|枢密院]]。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.number10.gov.uk/news/peerages-honours-and-appointments/ |title=Peerages, honours and appointments Number 10 |trans_title=首相府的任命、荣誉和册封 |publisher=Number10.gov.uk |date=2010-05-28 |accessdate=2012-11-07 |archive-date=2012-11-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121103191409/http://www.number10.gov.uk/news/peerages-honours-and-appointments/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://privycouncil.independent.gov.uk/privy-council/privy-council-members/privy-counsellors/#g |title=Privy Counsellors | Privy Council |trans_title=枢密院顾问官 |publisher=Privycouncil.independent.gov.uk |date= |accessdate=2012-11-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111221115352/http://privycouncil.independent.gov.uk/privy-council/privy-council-members/privy-counsellors/#g |archive-date=2011-12-21 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>格雷林从2010年<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.number10.gov.uk/news/topstorynews/2010/05/her-majestys-government-49840 |title=Her Majesty’s Government |trans_title=女王陛下的政府 |publisher=Number10.gov.uk |date=2010-05-19 |accessdate=2010-11-13 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100515034600/http://www.number10.gov.uk/news/topstorynews/2010/05/her-majestys-government-49840 |archivedate=2010-05-15 }}</ref>到2012年9月4日晋升内阁[[大法官_(英國)|大法官]]兼[[司法大臣_(英国)|司法大臣]]之前，担任工作和养老金部副大臣，负责职业介绍中心的工作。期间采取运营降低成本，在全国各地的办事处只留下10万名工作人员的措施引发争议。在“破碎社会”的背景下，他被一些一代又一代经常失业、住在内城{{le|下沉社区|Sink estate}}的家庭起诉。为了限制福利支出，格雷林还削减了本部门的预算。

该政策后来改革了囚犯的待遇，剥夺其投票权，并减少了监狱中的虐待行为。他宣布了囚犯工作方案，结束服刑人员“无所事事的文化”。他还收紧了一项价值50亿英镑的工作方案的规则以求更多长期失业坐享福利的人出门工作。<ref>{{cite web |last=Peacock |first=Louisa |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/jobs/9434461/Employment-Minister-Chris-Grayling-moves-to-push-more-people-on-benefits-back-into-work.html |title=Back to Work program |trans_title=回去工作方案 |publisher=Telegraph.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2016-07-29 |archive-date=2020-11-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201113041334/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/jobs/9434461/Employment-Minister-Chris-Grayling-moves-to-push-more-people-on-benefits-back-into-work.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

=== 司法大臣 ===
2012年10月1日，他在威斯敏斯特大教堂作为大法官宣誓就职，<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.justice.gov.uk/news/features/chris-grayling-sworn-in-as-lord-chancellor|title=Chris Grayling sworn in as Lord Chancellor|trans_title=格雷林宣誓就职大法官|work=justice.gov.uk|accessdate=2016-12-31|archive-date=2012-11-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121116012510/http://www.justice.gov.uk/news/features/chris-grayling-sworn-in-as-lord-chancellor|dead-url=no}}</ref>他于2012年12月11日当选为[[格雷律师学院|格雷律师学院]]的名誉院长，部分原因是他缺乏法律资质。成為繼1672年－1673年的{{link-en|安東尼·阿什利·庫珀，第一代沙夫茨伯里伯爵||沙夫茨伯里伯爵}}大法官之後，<ref name=scots>{{cite web|url=http://www.scotsman.com/news/queen-s-speech-sketch-ceremony-changes-1-2923263|title=Queen’s speech sketch: ceremony changes|trans_title=女王演讲：仪式的变化|work=scotsman.com|accessdate=2015-05-12|archive-date=2016-03-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160321182045/http://www.scotsman.com/news/queen-s-speech-sketch-ceremony-changes-1-2923263|dead-url=no}}</ref>440年來首位非律師出身的人物擔任大法官（然而伯爵在1638年曾考上[[林肯律師學院|林肯律師學院]]<ref name=HOP>{{cite web|url=http://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1660-1690/member/cooper-sir-anthony-ashley-1621-83|title=COOPER,   Sir Anthony Ashley, 2nd Bt. (1621–83),  of Wimborne St. Giles, Dorset and The Close, Salisbury, Wilts.|work=historyofparliamentonline.org|accessdate=2016-12-31|archive-date=2020-10-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201021023854/http://historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1660-1690/member/cooper-sir-anthony-ashley-1621-83|dead-url=no}}</ref>）。格雷林的任命被广泛认为是回到比他的前任[[肯尼斯·克拉克|肯尼斯·克拉克]]更强硬的方法。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2012/sep/20/chris-grayling-take-hardline-prison|title=Chris Grayling takes hard line on prison|trans_title=克里斯·格雷林在监狱问题方面更强硬|work=the Guardian|accessdate=2016-12-31|archive-date=2020-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111172212/http://www.theguardian.com/politics/2012/sep/20/chris-grayling-take-hardline-prison|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/law-and-order/9554533/Prison-should-be-tougher-for-criminals-Justice-Secretary-Chris-Grayling-warns.html | location=London | work=The Daily Telegraph | title=Prison should be tougher for criminals, Justice Secretary Chris Grayling warns | trans_title=监狱应该对罪犯更加严厉，司法大臣克里斯·格林林警告 | date=2012-09-20 | accessdate=2016-12-31 | archive-date=2019-05-15 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190515162655/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/law-and-order/9554533/Prison-should-be-tougher-for-criminals-Justice-Secretary-Chris-Grayling-warns.html | dead-url=no }}</ref> 事实上格雷林追求“强硬正义”议程，包括结束恐怖分子和儿童强奸犯的自动提前释放，<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/law-and-order/10354553/Chris-Grayling-to-end-early-release-for-child-rapists-and-terrorists.html | location=London | work=The Daily Telegraph | first=Steven | last=Swinford | title=Chris Grayling to end early release for child rapists and terrorists | trans_title=克里斯·格雷林结束提前释放儿童强奸犯和恐怖分子 | date=2013-10-04 | accessdate=2016-12-31 | archive-date=2019-05-15 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190515144315/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/law-and-order/10354553/Chris-Grayling-to-end-early-release-for-child-rapists-and-terrorists.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>结束严重罪行的简单警告，<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/news/chris-grayling-simple-cautions-for-serious-offences-to-be-scrapped|title=Chris Grayling: Simple cautions for serious offences to be scrapped|trans_title=克里斯·格林林：严重的罪行简单的警告要报废|work=www.gov.uk|accessdate=2016-12-31|archive-date=2019-07-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190724011006/https://www.gov.uk/government/news/chris-grayling-simple-cautions-for-serious-offences-to-be-scrapped|dead-url=no}}</ref>并对为抵御入侵者而自卫的住户提供更大的保护。<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-19879314 | work=BBC News | title=Conservative conference: Force against burglars to be allowed | trans_title=保守党年会：强制防盗合法 | date=2012-10-09 | accessdate=2016-12-31 | archive-date=2020-11-11 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111185553/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-19879314 | dead-url=no }}</ref>知名人权律师[[彭力克|彭力克]]描述了格林的表现“他的企图只有限制司法审查和人权，他没有保护司法机构免受他同事的批评并将将法律援助减至最低限度。”<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/andy-mcsmiths-diary-chris-grayling-the-worst-lord-chancellor-for-342-years-no-worse-10114748.html|title=Andy McSmith's Diary: Chris Grayling the worst Lord Chancellor for 342 years? No, worse|trans_title=Andy McSmith的日记：格雷林是最342年来糟糕的大法官吗？不，更糟|first=Andy|last=Smith|work=The Independent|date=2017-03-17|accessdate=2016-07-25|archive-date=2019-05-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190518011942/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/andy-mcsmiths-diary-chris-grayling-the-worst-lord-chancellor-for-342-years-no-worse-10114748.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==== 囚犯改革 ====
格雷林在[[英國司法部|司法部]]的第一个行动是开始一个项目，改变罪犯的改造方式，以减少重犯率。在“[[按成果评定资制|按成果评定资制]]”制度下，私人公司和[[慈善组织|慈善组织]]在社区看管犯罪者方面发挥更大的作用。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/speeches/rehabilitation-revolution-the-next-steps|title=Rehabilitation revolution: the next steps|trans_title=恢复正常生活革命：下一步|work=www.gov.uk|accessdate=2016-12-31|archive-date=2019-09-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190919080054/https://www.gov.uk/government/speeches/rehabilitation-revolution-the-next-steps|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-22886395 | work=BBC News | title=Prison payment-by-results schemes see reoffending cut | trans_title=监狱按成果评定资制重新裁员 | date=2013-06-13 | accessdate=2016-12-31 | archive-date=2020-10-21 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201021024955/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-22886395 | dead-url=no }}</ref>格雷林禁止书籍2送进监狱的做法引来刑事改革推进组织和作家[[菲利普·普尔曼|菲利普·普尔曼]]、[[安東尼·霍洛維茨|安東尼·霍洛維茨]]、[[艾玛·多诺霍|艾玛·多诺霍]]等的广泛批评。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/books/news/authors-blast-chris-graylings-vindictive-act-of-banning-prisoners-from-receiving-books-9212921.html|title=Authors blast Chris Grayling's 'vindictive act' of banning prisoners from receiving books|trans_title=作家批评克里斯·格雷林的禁止囚犯接收书籍的做法|first=Chris|last=Green|date=2014-03-24|work=The Independent|accessdate=2016-12-31|archive-date=2014-12-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141219062833/http://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/books/news/authors-blast-chris-graylings-vindictive-act-of-banning-prisoners-from-receiving-books-9212921.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>这项禁令被人称为“可憎的”。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://jonsjailjournal.blogspot.co.uk/2014/03/banning-books-from-uk-prisoners-is.html|title=Jon's Jail Journal (by Shaun Attwood)|author=Jon|work=jonsjailjournal.blogspot.co.uk|accessdate=2016-12-31|archive-date=2017-12-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201040147/http://jonsjailjournal.blogspot.co.uk/2014/03/banning-books-from-uk-prisoners-is.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

这个禁令被辩护为不是关于禁止书被送入监狱，而是关于包裹被送进，因为允许后者进入监狱几乎肯定会增加违禁品进入监狱的数量。<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/law-and-order/10742660/Nasty-Chris-Grayling-is-fighting-to-bring-the-justice-blob-to-book.html | location=London | work=The Daily Telegraph | first=Isabel | last=Hardman | title=Nasty Chris Grayling is fighting to bring the justice 'blob' to book | trans_title=格雷林争取把正义滴进书中 | date=2014-04-03 | accessdate=2016-12-31 | archive-date=2020-01-04 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200104042234/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/law-and-order/10742660/Nasty-Chris-Grayling-is-fighting-to-bring-the-justice-blob-to-book.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>退休的{{le|监狱总监察长|Her Majesty's Chief Inspector of Prisons}}尼克·哈德威克批评格雷林的“强烈地”干扰报告的内容和格雷林的部门使用财务控制来影响检查，从而威胁监察专员的独立性。<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/nick-hardwick-prisons-inspector-steps-down-with-attack-on-chris-grayling-for-trying-to-influence-his-a6824041.html|title= Nick Hardwick: Prisons inspector steps down with attack on Chris Grayling for trying to influence his work|trans_title= 尼克·哈德威克：前监狱监察长攻击克里斯·格雷林试图影响他的工作|work= The Independent|date= 2016-01-20|accessdate= 2016-01-30|archive-date= 2019-05-19|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20190519201053/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/nick-hardwick-prisons-inspector-steps-down-with-attack-on-chris-grayling-for-trying-to-influence-his-a6824041.html|dead-url= no}}</ref> 

==== 监狱基准测试和裁减员额 ====
格雷林在2012年引入了一项监狱“基准”计划，降低公共监狱的成本以匹敌的私营监狱，以及相关的新核心标准，旨在使囚犯在类似监狱中在囚室外面活动时间相近。<ref name="guardian-20140429">{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/2014/apr/29/prisons-ordered-cust-costs-149-million-a-year |title=Prisons governors ordered to cut costs by £149m a year |trans_title=监狱长命令每年减少成本1.49亿英镑 |author=Alan Travis, Steven Morris |newspaper=The Guardian |date=2014-04-29 |accessdate=2016-11-17 |archive-date=2020-11-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112031507/http://www.theguardian.com/society/2014/apr/29/prisons-ordered-cust-costs-149-million-a-year |dead-url=no }}</ref>监狱官员人数从2012年的约23000人减少到2015年的约18000人。<ref name="bbc-20161103">{{cite news |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-37854358 |title=Prisons to get 'biggest overhaul in a generation' |trans_title=监狱得到“一代最大的大修” |work=BBC News |date=2016-11-03 |accessdate=2016-11-17 |archive-date=2020-11-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108124216/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-37854358 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

在2015年，{{le|下院司法委员会|Justice Select Committee}}在经过长达一年的监狱调查之后，就自2012年以来监狱死亡人数上升38％的情况对司法大臣们表示批评。委员会得出结论，增效节支和人员短缺对监狱中的“安全恶化”作出了重大推波助澜的作用。<ref name="guardian-20150318">{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/2015/mar/18/uk-justice-minister-chris-grayling-complacent-38-rise-in-prison-deaths-say-mps |title=UK justice minister 'complacent' over 38% rise in prison deaths, say MPs |trans_title=英国司法大臣“自满”，监狱死亡人数增加了38％以上 |author=Alan Travis |newspaper=The Guardian |date=2015-03-18 |accessdate=2016-11-17 |archive-date=2020-02-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200216020948/https://www.theguardian.com/society/2015/mar/18/uk-justice-minister-chris-grayling-complacent-38-rise-in-prison-deaths-say-mps |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="hoc-20150318">{{cite news |url=http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201415/cmselect/cmjust/309/309.pdf |title=Prisons: planning and policies |trans_title=监狱：规划和政策 |publisher=UK Parliament |work=House of Commons Justice Committee |id=HC 309 |date=2015-03-18 |accessdate=2016-11-17 |archive-date=2020-02-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200210082532/https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201415/cmselect/cmjust/309/309.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>

