==== 司法部安全漏洞 ====
在2015年1月，司法部丢失了三起致命的警察枪击案件材料，包括射手和死者家属的详细资料。据卫报说，这使格雷林尤其尴尬，因为政府声称它需要监控个人数据来应对恐怖主义，并可以安全地保存它。丢失的材料还包括引发了[[2011年英国骚乱|2011年英格兰暴乱]]的马克·杜根枪击事件的细节。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2015/jan/29/file-mark-duggan-police-shooting-lost-post|work=the Guardian|title=File on Mark Duggan police shooting lost in the post|trans_title=马克·杜根枪击事件的资料被政府丢失|first=Vikram|last=Dodd|date=2015-01-29|accessdate=2015-01-30|archive-date=2020-01-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200105221201/https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2015/jan/29/file-mark-duggan-police-shooting-lost-post|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 下议院领袖 ===
在[[2015年英国大选|2015年大选]]后，格雷林被任命为下议院领袖和枢密院议长。[[迈克尔·戈夫|迈克尔·戈夫]]接替格雷林为司法大臣和大法官，<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.bbc.com/news/election-2015-32679004|title = Michael Gove moves to justice in post-election reshuffle|trans_title = 迈克尔·戈夫在大选后内阁重组中调任司法部|last = |first = |date = 2015-05-09|work = |access-date = 2015-05-10|via = BBC News|archive-date = 2020-10-23|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201023052310/https://www.bbc.com/news/election-2015-32679004|dead-url = no}}</ref>据说格雷林对此次“履新”没有任何压力。<ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Criminal courts charge to be scrapped by government |trans_title=刑事法院指控被政府报废 |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-34993428 |newspaper=BBC News |location= |date=2015-12-03 |access-date=2015-12-03 |archive-date=2020-11-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108141702/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-34993428 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

=== 运输大臣 ===
[[File:Secretary_of_State_for_Transport_Chris_Grayling_call_on_Tokyo_Governor_Koike_(29373569403).jpg|thumb]]会面]]
格雷林被新的首相[[特蕾莎·梅|特蕾莎·梅]]于2016年7月任命为运输大臣。<ref>{{cite news |first=Julia |last=Rampen |url=http://www.newstatesman.com/politics/staggers/2016/07/theresa-may-s-first-cabinet-glance |title=Theresa May’s first Cabinet at a glance |trans_title=第一次梅内阁一览 |work=New Statesman |date=2016-07-14 |accessdate=2016-07-29 |archive-date=2020-11-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108141626/http://www.newstatesman.com/politics/staggers/2016/07/theresa-may-s-first-cabinet-glance |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/dec/19/chris-grayling-tory-combative-mood-deal-with-rail-union-bosses Chris Grayling: Tory in combative mood to deal with rail union bosses] {{Wayback|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/dec/19/chris-grayling-tory-combative-mood-deal-with-rail-union-bosses |date=20200108211255 }} Published by The Guardian 19, December, 2016</ref>在2016年12月，他阻止了大伦敦市长[[萨迪克·汗|萨迪克·汗]]的行动，以控制由伦敦交通局运营的伦敦东南部地铁服务。泄漏的信件显示，在2013年，格雷林写给时任伦敦市长[[鲍里斯·约翰逊|鲍里斯·约翰逊]]说，他反对这种行动，因为把这些服务会被“工党市长抓在手里”。这使格雷林被指控将党派利益置于公众和通勤者的利益之上，他的个别保守党同事甚至要求他辞职。<ref>{{cite news|last1=Mason|first1=Rowena|title=Rail letter leak: Chris Grayling accused of putting politics over people|trans_title=铁路泄漏：克里斯·格雷林被指责，把政治置于人之上|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2016/dec/07/chris-grayling-accused-of-putting-politics-over-people-in-rail-letter-leak|accessdate=2016-12-17|work=The Guardian|date=2016-12-07|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112011430/https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2016/dec/07/chris-grayling-accused-of-putting-politics-over-people-in-rail-letter-leak|dead-url=no}}</ref><br />
他也因2016年10月在威斯敏斯特{{le|打开大臣的车门|Dooring}}撞伤骑车人而受到批评。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/dec/16/chris-grayling-could-face-private-prosecution-for-dooring-cyclist|title=Chris Grayling could face private prosecution for ‘dooring’ cyclist|trans_title=克里斯·格雷林可能面临骑车人的私人起诉|first=Gwyn|last=Topham|date=2016-12-16|accessdate=2016-12-17|work=The Guardian|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108114947/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/dec/16/chris-grayling-could-face-private-prosecution-for-dooring-cyclist|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-38340125|title=Chris Grayling knocked cyclist off bike outside Parliament|trans_title=克里斯·格雷林骑在国会外面撞伤骑自行车的人|date=2016-12-16|publisher=BBC News|accessdate=2016-12-17|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108103114/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-38340125|dead-url=no}}</ref>

